14 (c) Ten judicial days after the entry of a court order which
15 denies the action for summary eviction; [or
16 (c)] (d) Thirty-one days after the tenant has filed an affidavit
17 described in subsection 3 of NRS 40.253 or subsection 3 of NRS
18 40.2542, if the landlord has failed to file an affidavit of complaint
19 pursuant to subsection 5 of NRS 40.253 or subsection 5 of NRS
20 40.2542 within 30 days after the tenant filed the affidavit [.] ; or
21 (e) If an appeal is taken, upon a district court, the Court of
22 Appeals or the Supreme Court of Nevada, whichever has
23 jurisdiction over the matter, rendering a decision that:
24 (1) Upholds an order which dismisses an action for
25 summary eviction;
26 (2) Upholds an order which denies an action for summary
27 eviction; or
28 (3) Remands the case to the court from which the appeal
29 was taken for the entry of an order which:
30 (I) Dismisses an action for summary eviction; or
31 (II) Denies an action for summary eviction.
